{"article_id":"wO5tAv9l5li4e5Vz","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Anti-government protests have rocked Hong Kong for months","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"and the situation shows no sign of dying down .","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"Here 's all the background","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"you need to know","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"in 100 or 500 words","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"- you can read each individually or in turn .","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"Hong Kong 's protests started in June against plans","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"to allow extradition to mainland China .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"Critics feared","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"this could undermine judicial independence","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"and endanger dissidents .","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"Until 1997 , Hong Kong was ruled by Britain as a colony","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"but then returned to China .","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"Under the `` one country , two systems '' arrangement , it has some autonomy , and its people more rights .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"The bill was withdrawn in September","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"but demonstrations continue","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"and now demand full democracy and an inquiry into police actions .","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"Clashes between police and activists have become increasingly violent ,","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"with police firing live bullets","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"and protesters attacking officers","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"and throwing petrol bombs .","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"The extradition bill","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"which triggered the first protest","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"was introduced in April .","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"It would have allowed for criminal suspects to be extradited to mainland China under certain circumstances .","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"Opponents said","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"this risked exposing Hongkongers to unfair trials and violent treatment .","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"They also argued","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"the bill would give China greater influence over Hong Kong","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"and could be used","depth":13},{"id":30,"text":"to target activists and journalists .","depth":13},{"id":31,"text":"Hundreds of thousands of people took to the streets .","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"After weeks of protests , leader Carrie Lam eventually said","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"the bill would be suspended indefinitely .","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"Protesters feared","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"the bill could be revived ,","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"so demonstrations continued ,","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"calling for it to be withdrawn completely .","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"By then clashes between police and protesters had become more frequent and violent .","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"In September , the bill was finally withdrawn ,","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"but protesters said","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"this was `` too little , too late '' .","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"On 1 October ,","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"while China was celebrating 70 years of Communist Party rule ,","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"Hong Kong experienced one of its most `` violent and chaotic days '' .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"An 18-year-old was shot in the chest with a live bullet","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"as protesters fought officers with poles , petrol bombs and other projectiles .","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"The government then banned protesters","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"wearing face masks ,","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"and in early November a pro-Beijing lawmaker was stabbed in the street by a man","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"pretending to be a supporter .","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"One week later , a policeman shot one protester at close range","depth":13},{"id":52,"text":"when activists were trying to set up a road block .","depth":13},{"id":53,"text":"Later that day another man was set on fire by anti-government protesters .","depth":13},{"id":54,"text":"In November , a standoff between police and students","depth":15},{"id":55,"text":"barricaded on the campus of Hong Kong 's Polytechnic University","depth":15},{"id":56,"text":"became another defining moment .","depth":14},{"id":57,"text":"Later that month , the territory held local council elections","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"that were seen as a barometer of public opinion .","depth":13},{"id":59,"text":"The vote saw a landslide victory for the pro-democracy movement ,","depth":13},{"id":60,"text":"with 17 of the 18 councils now controlled by pro-democracy councillors .","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"Some protesters have adopted the motto :","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"`` Five demands , not one less ! ''","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"These are :","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"For the protests not to be characterised as a `` riot ''","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"The fifth demand , the withdrawal of the bill , has already been met .","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"Protests","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"supporting the Hong Kong movement","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"have spread across the globe ,","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"with rallies taking place in the UK , France , US , Canada and Australia .","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"In many cases , people","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"supporting the demonstrators","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"were confronted by pro-Beijing rallies .","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"Chinese president Xi Jinping has warned against separatism ,","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"any attempt","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"to divide China","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"would end in `` bodies smashed","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"and bones ground to powder '' .","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"Hong Kong is a former British colony","depth":4},{"id":80,"text":"handed back to China in 1997 .","depth":4},{"id":81,"text":"It has its own judiciary and a separate legal system from mainland China .","depth":4},{"id":82,"text":"Those rights include freedom of assembly and freedom of speech .","depth":5},{"id":83,"text":"But those freedoms","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"- the Basic Law -","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"expire in 2047","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"and it is not clear what Hong Kong 's status will then be .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":173,"left":88,"right":172,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":88,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":172,"left":164,"right":171,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":164,"left":91,"right":163,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":91,"left":90,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":90,"left":89,"right":4,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":89,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":163,"left":105,"right":162,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":105,"left":95,"right":104,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":95,"left":92,"right":94,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":92,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":94,"left":8,"right":93,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":93,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":104,"left":97,"right":103,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":97,"left":96,"right":13,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":96,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":103,"left":99,"right":102,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":99,"left":14,"right":98,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":98,"left":15,"right":16,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":102,"left":17,"right":101,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":18,"right":100,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":100,"left":19,"right":20,"relation":"joint